name: •  The Life and The Self  •
description: The absurdity is born of this confrontation between the human appeal and the unreasonable silence of the world. That is what must not be forgotten. That is what we must hold on to, because the whole consequence of a life can be born from it. The irrational, the human longing and the absurdity that arises from their face to face, here are the three characters of the drama that must necessarily end with all the logic that an existence is capable of.
